  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      Cardiac magnetic resonance imaging has emerged as a potential valuable test for the early
      detection of Pulmonary Arterial Hypertension. A number of reports have provided some
      preliminary evidence that Pulmonary Artery (PA) stiffness may be accurately detected by
      imaging of the pulmonary artery in order to measure PA stiffness. In addition, cardiac MRI
      could play provide early and effective treatment for Pulmonary Arterial Hypertension (PAH).
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
